## What is Loss Function?

Loss function measures how much the model prediction is wrong compared to the actual value.

Small loss â†’ Good prediction
Large loss â†’ Bad prediction

Model training process:
Predict â†’ Calculate Loss â†’ Update Weights â†’ Improve Prediction

---

## Example (Customer Churn)

Actual = 1 (Customer leaves)
Prediction = 0.9 â†’ Small loss (Correct)
Prediction = 0.1 â†’ Large loss (Wrong)

---

## Loss Function Used in This Project

We use **Binary Crossentropy** because output is binary:
Churn = 1
No Churn = 0

It checks how close the predicted probability is to the real answer.

---

## Key Point

Loss Function tells the model **how bad it is**.
Optimizer tells the model **how to improve**.
